        <h2 id="faq">Frequently asked questions</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What is the best programmatic SEO tool in 2026?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>It depends on the pSEO approach. For done-for-you content pSEO (city + service pages, comparison pages), theStacc at $99/mo. For AI-driven bulk article generation, Byword. For template-driven pages from a data table, Whalesync, SEOmatic, or PageFactory. For a custom Airtable + Webflow stack, the no-code DIY route.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What is the difference between programmatic SEO and bulk content?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Programmatic SEO uses templates and structured data to generate hundreds or thousands of pages that target long-tail queries — think Zapier's app-integration pages or G2's category pages. Bulk content is just publishing many AI-written articles. Programmatic is template-driven; bulk is AI-prompt-driven. Both can scale, but they have different ranking patterns.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Does programmatic SEO still work after Google's spam updates?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Yes — when the pages provide unique value. Zapier, G2, and Nomad List still rank thousands of programmatic pages because each one answers a specific user query with structured data the user actually wants. Thin templated pages that just spin variables got hit by the helpful content updates and continue to get hit.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Do I need to be technical to do programmatic SEO?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Not anymore. PageFactory, SEOmatic, and Whalesync let you connect Airtable or Google Sheets to your CMS without code. theStacc removes the data-modelling step entirely — you tell it the topic, it generates the data and the pages. The technical bar in 2026 is much lower than it was even two years ago.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Is theStacc a true programmatic SEO tool?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
